### 1. Register a Webhook Endpoint
# This simulates a client (like an e-commerce store) telling us: 
# "Hey, send webhooks to my URL!"
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/endpoints
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://webhook.site/#!/view/YOUR-WEBHOOK-SITE-ID-HERE",
  "secretKey": "my-super-secret-key"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("endpointId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### 2. Subscribe the Endpoint to an Event Type
# This tells our system: "Only send 'payment.success' events to Endpoint 1"
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/endpoints/{{endpointId}}/subscriptions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "payment.success"
}

###

### 3. Publish an Event (Trigger the Webhook!)
# This simulates our internal system (like a billing service) saying:
# "A payment was successful! Tell all subscribers!"
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "payment.success",
  "idempotencyKey": "unique-payment-12345",
  "payload": {
    "orderId": "ORD-999",
    "amount": 250.50,
    "currency": "USD",
    "customerEmail": "test@example.com"
  }
}

###

### 4. Check Delivery History
# View the history of webhooks sent to this endpoint
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries/history/{{endpointId}}?page=0&size=10

###

### 5. Test Exponential Backoff (Force Failure)
# Register a broken URL that doesn't exist to watch RabbitMQ retry!
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/endpoints
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://localhost:9999/this-will-fail",
  "secretKey": "fail-key"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("failEndpointId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### 6. Subscribe Broken Endpoint
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/endpoints/{{failEndpointId}}/subscriptions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "user.created"
}

###

### 7. Trigger Event for Broken Endpoint (Watch the console logs!)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventType": "user.created",
  "idempotencyKey": "unique-user-999",
  "payload": {
    "userId": "USR-123"
  }
}
